ca.uqac.lif.ecp.statechart

Class NestedState<T extends Event>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uqac.lif.ecp.statechart.State<T>
      • ca.uqac.lif.ecp.statechart.NestedState<T>

  • public class NestedState<T extends Event>
extends State<T>
    A state that encloses multiple statecharts. Graphically, it is represented as a box that contains other states and transitions. If the nested state contains multiple statecharts, these are interpreted as orthogonal regions.
    Author:
    Sylvain Hall√©

      • getAnyAtomicChild

        public State<T> getAnyAtomicChild()
        Returns an arbitrary state inside this nested state that is not a NestedState. The method recurses inside statecharts. This method is mostly used for the graphical rendering of a statechart.
        Returns:
        A state, or null if no such state exists
